{"id":101,"parent_id":96,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":101,"title":"Acts 5: Delivered from Prison","subtitle":"","short_title":"Acts 5: Delivered from Prison","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison"},[".heading",{"id":"head6","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison.head6"},["h1","Acts 5"],[".subtitle","Delivered from Prison"],[".intro","Have you noticed that life is full of trials? It comes as no surprise when the wicked have troubles, but the righteous have been told that they too must endure trials and temptation (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/14.22"},"Acts 14:22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/1.12"},"James 1:12"],"). Overcoming these trials results in exaltation for the righteous (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.3"},"Alma 36:3"],")."],[".intro",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5"},"Acts 5"],"contains a good illustration of this principle. The Apostles knew that if they continued to uphold truth they would face great difficulty. But compare what happened to them with what happened to Ananias and Sapphira, who chose not to do what was right."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f25","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison.f25"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5"},"Acts 5"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Being privy to"],"(v. 2)"],["td","Knowing about"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Conceived"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Thought"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Wound him up"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Wrapped his dead body in cloth"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Indignation"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Self-righteous anger, jealousy"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Keepers standing without"],"(v. 23)"],["td","Guards standing outside"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Doubted of them whereunto this would grow"],"(v. 24)"],["td","Wondered how this would turn out"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Take heed to yourselves"],"(v. 35)"],["td","Think carefully"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Brought to nought, come to nought"],"(vv. 36, 38)"],["td","Not amount to anything"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p117","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison.p117"},"Do activities A and B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5"},"Acts 5"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Apostles in Prison Again!"],[".figure",{"id":"f26","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison.f26"},["p.preamble","Below you will find possible newspaper headlines for the story in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.12-32"},"Acts 5:12–32"],"about the Apostles going to prison again. Compare each headline to the story and write a sentence or two explaining what the headline means."],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Crowds Gather for Healings (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.16"},"v. 16"],")"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Innocent Men in Prison (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.18"},"v. 18"],")"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","Miraculous Jailbreak (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.22"},"v. 22"],")"]],["li",["span.label","4."],["p.para","Christians Defy the High Priest (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.29"},"v. 29"],")"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"What Was He Thinking?"],["p.para",{"id":"p122","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-acts-of-the-apostles/acts-5-delivered-from-prison.p122"},"Review",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.34-42"},"Acts 5:34–42"],". Write an entry in your notebook as if you had been there with Peter. Report the actions of the council, especially of Gamaliel, and explain what you think Gamaliel meant."]]]]]]],"refs":null}
